This pull request makes it a bit easier to build off of mx.io.ImageIter to make your own image iters by pulling out some code out into their own functions.

Example:

```
class RandImageIter(mx.image.ImageIter):
    
    def check_data_shape(self, data_shape):
        if not len(data_shape) == 3:
            raise ValueError('data_shape should have length 3, with dimensions CxHxW')
        if not data_shape[0] == 1:
            raise ValueError('This iterator expects inputs to have 3 channels.')
    
    def imdecode(self, s):
        return mx.nd.array(s)
    
    def read_image(self, fname):
        #fname is disregarded for brevity in example    
        return np.random.random(self.data_shape[::-1])
```
